	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#33;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Mobile</placeName> <date>August 27 1848</date>.</p>
				<p>Your favour from <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst.&#44; with acknowledgment<lb/> of the &#36;20 00 in check on Pensilvan<add>&#63;</add> Bank came to<lb/> Hand.  I have according your Request&#44; inquired of<lb/> <persName>Mr. Bowlumet<add>&#63;</add></persName> in Reference to the Books you send in<lb/> his care for <persName>A Englander</persName>&#44; he informs me that he for<lb/><sic>wardet</sic> the same to a <persName>Mr Pfister</persName> Bookseller in <placeName>Montgome<lb/>ry</placeName> for deliverance&#44; but as <persName>Mr Englander</persName> has left since<lb/> <date>April</date> for <placeName>Germany</placeName> &#38; <persName>Mr Englander</persName> is at present absent<lb/> from <placeName>Montgomery</placeName>.  I have instructed <persName>Mr H. Lehman</persName> from<lb/> <persName>M.</persName> the Treasurer of the congregation to receive the Books<lb/> from <persName>Mr Pfister</persName> or to deliver the same to all who may<lb/> want any &#38; receive the money for the same.  <persName>Mr De Silva</persName><lb/> says that he hath written to you about the Books &#38; <sic>sayd</sic><lb/> something about a Deduction on the same on account being<lb/> damaged.  In Reference to those Gent&#58; who are in arrears for<lb/> the <sic>occident</sic> I will exert myself to collect the money&#44; but<lb/> I doubt if any will pay until they come here in Fall.  I shall<lb/> nevertheless write to them about it.  The are all good &#38; will<lb/> pay some Times.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have sold &#38; engaged all the Prayerbooks but <del>as</del> I<lb/> have not rec. any payments&#44; yet.  I could sell probably several<lb/> copies more say 6 or 8 of those c &#36;2 50. if I hath them<lb/> here.  If you mind to send any you may do so&#44; &#38; as <persName>Mr Y<lb/> Kayser</persName> probable sends out some <add>&#63;</add> to me&#44; you could<lb/> without</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>incurring any expenses send the along &#38; if you have any<lb/> Jewish calendars you will send me a few doz.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr I Newman</persName> &#38; <persName>P. Myers</persName> have recd the <sic>occident</sic> since<lb/> I wrote to you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><sic>I</sic> conclusion&#44; I remark that you owe me no thanks &#38; are under<lb/> no obligation to me whatever <del>&#63;</del> for the little trouble<lb/> I have if any in gaining for you subscribers for the <sic>occident</sic><lb/> or in effecting some sales for your religious books.  I am free<lb/> to confess&#44; that&#44; although I shall always feel happy to confer<lb/> a favour or serve in any manner my fellow Neighbour particular<lb/> a fellow believer&#44; yet my prime object is in the above&#44; to arouse<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add> <add>&#63;</add> from that fatal indifference about their Religion<lb/> in which they are alas&#44; so fearfully sunk &#38; this is the main<lb/> cause why I am so desirous of spreading among them some<lb/> good &#38; religious works like the <sic>occident</sic>&#59; but if in doing<lb/> so&#44; I can or do serve you in any way I shall feel most happy<lb/> but as above stated the prime object is <del>in doing so</del> a desire<lb/> of doing some good in <placeName>Israel</placeName>&#44; or if I <sic>incidently</sic> serve you it<lb/> is not the primary object consequently you owe me nothing.<lb/>  I desire no thanks &#38; neither Reward.</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)">I am my dear sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Yours very truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><persName role="author">B M Emanuel</persName></p>
				<p>P. S. If I can serve you</p>
				<p>in any thing or transaction which</p>
				<p>you may have here in the <placeName>south</placeName></p>
				<p>you are always welcome to write to me</p>
				<p>about it&#44; I shall cheerfully attend to any thing</p>
				<p>you may require</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee> Editor of</p>
				<p>Occident &#38; <sic>american</sic> <sic>jewish</sic> Advocate</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
